                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>Madam Skerzana holds aloft her antique silver mirror and gazes through it into the past or future of a creature within 30 feet, infusing its thoughts with visions of their helplessness as a new-born baby or of a potential death from violence or peril in the future. Madam Skerzana chooses if she's showing the past or the future when she uses Mirror Gaze. The targeted creature must attempt a @Check[will|dc:26] save or become affected as indicated below, depending on which vision Madam Skerzana chose to impart.</p>\n<p><strong>The Past</strong> A glowing green eye momentarily opens on the right side of Madam Skerzana's face, and the target creature becomes @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Stupefied]{Stupefied 1} (@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Stupefied]{Stupefied 2} on a critical failure) as their mind reverts to a limited infantile intellect. At the end of the character's turn, the value of this stupefied condition decreases by 1.</p>\n<p><strong>The Future</strong> A glowing blue eye momentarily opens on the left side of Madam Skerzana's face, and the target creature becomes @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Frightened]{Frightened 1} (@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Frightened]{Frightened 2} on a critical failure) as their mind reels from a harrowing vision of their imminent death. Describe this death vision to the PC briefly, choosing one of the Arudoras that the party has yet to encounter and defeat. When that PC encounters that Arudora later in the campaign, they must attempt a new @Check[will|dc:26|options:inflicts:frightened] save to avoid becoming frightened 1 (frightened 2 on a critical failure) all over again.</p>"
                },
